data.title: One Life To Live: Josh Kelly Recast As Joey Buchanan. (UPDATED!)

data.text:
A new face for Joey!

Updated on November 16:

ABC Soaps In Depth is reporting that Josh Kelly’s character’s name is Cutter. He will first appear at the end of the year and be involved in the storyline surrounding the Joey/Kelly/Aubrey triangle.

Updated on October 7:

There’s just been a huge casting change-up at ABC. Tom Degnan Is In, Josh Kelly Is Out As Joey Buchanan. However, the show has hired Josh for another contract role that Soaps.com will update our readers on as soon as details are released. Stay tuned!

Previously Reported on October 5:

Joey Buchanan is about to make his way back to Llanview. ABC Soaps In Depth is reporting that One Life to Live has just recast the role with Josh Kelly who will first arrive on the scene on Wednesday November 24 just in time to celebrate the holidays!

Fans may recognize Josh from his role in “Transformers: Revenge Of The Fallen,” as well as Primetime shows to include “Flash Forward,” “True Blood” and he appeared as Felix in 2006’s “Desire.” However, aside from Josh’s acting credits, he’s a former Army Ranger who served three tours in Afghanistan and one in Iraq. As a side note, Josh is not to be mistake for former Grey’s Anatomy star Katherine Heigl’s husband Josh Kelley, with an E!
